quizzes.question:
What is the value of x after this code?
int x = 5;
int y = 3;
x = (x > y) ? y : x;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The ? : Operator[/h1]

Consider the following example: [code format="cs" codeId="851"]int age = 42;
string msg;
if(age >= 18)
  msg = "Welcome";
else
  msg = "Sorry";

Console.WriteLine(msg);[/code]
The code above checks the value of the [b]age [/b]variable and displays the corresponding message to the screen.
This can be done in a more elegant and shorter way by using the [b]?: operator[/b], which has the following form: [code format="cs" ]Exp1 [b]?[/b] Exp2 [b]:[/b] Exp3;[/code]
The ?: operator works the following way: Exp1 is evaluated. If it is true, then Exp2 is evaluated and becomes the value of the entire expression. If Exp1 is false, then Exp3 is evaluated and its value becomes the value of the expression.
So, the example above can be replaced by the following: [code format="cs" codeId="852"]int age = 42;
string msg;
[b]msg = (age >= 18) ? "Welcome" : "Sorry";[/b]
Console.WriteLine(msg);[/code]
